<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="0ed4594e-ae93-5df6-a6c3-6d01ee12f7a5" activityNameId="7b223111-2fb6-4723-ba4e-7a84ba9923e9" parentActivityId="c4479017-1163-55fe-8d13-20c9fcf8220b" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid production, alkaline cyanomethylation of ethylenediamine</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Edetic acid</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">EDTA</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Edathamil</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Endrate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">60-00-4</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The dataset includes the processing of the raw materials and chemicals used for production. It also includes estimated emissions to air and water from production (incomplete), as well as estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant (approximation). Solid wastes are omitted.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA). EDTA is nowadays a very important chelating agent. In the paper and pulp industry, EDTA is used to improve the brightness of the paper pulp bleached by H2O2 or sodium dithionite. Furthermore, EDTA can be used as a stabilizer and for metal ion control.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The industial production of EDTA is made nowadays with two different techniques – the alkaline cyanomethylation of ethylenediamine by sodium cyanide and formaldehyde, or the two-step Singer synthesis. For this dataset, the first technique is taken into consideration, as this is the most widely used synthesis method. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This dataset is based on literature data as well as data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">According to Hart (2000) the industial production of EDTA is made nowadays with two different techniques – the alkaline cyanomethylation of ethylenediamine by sodium cyanide and formaldehyde / two-step Singer synthesis. For this dataset, only the first production technique is taken into consideration, as it is the most widely used synthesis method. The overall reaction is the following:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">H2NCH2CH2NH2 + 4 CH2O + 4 NaCN + 4 H2O → (NaOOCCH2)2NCH2CH2N(CH2COONa)2 + 4 NH3</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">With this production method, very high yields (&gt; 90%) can be achieved. The by-product ammonia is usually boiled off during the reaction (Hart 2000).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">For this dataset, a process yield of 95% is assumed. The inventory is based on stoechiometric calculations. The emissions to air (0.2 wt% of raw material input) and water were estimated using mass balance. Treatment of the wastewater in an internal wastewater treatment plant is assumed (elimination efficiency of 90% for C).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Reference:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Hart R. J. (2000) Ethylenediaminetetraacetic Acid and Related Chelating Agents. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Sixth Edition, June-2001 Electronic Release (ed. Häussinger P., Leitgeb P. and Schmücker B.), 6 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version under: http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/ueic/ull_search_fs.html.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data in this dataset come from different years, but overall form the most realistic picture of the production. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="3a734293-7148-59ba-a845-d6f787159609" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="RP" casNumber="60-00-4" amount="1.0" intermediateExchangeId="a5d022c6-c879-416a-bb1a-51b8c2c87bb1" productionVolumeAmount="53900000.0" productionVolumeVariableName="RP_PV">
        <name xml:lang="en">EDTA, ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">EDTA is nowadays a very important chelating agent. In the paper and pulp industry, EDTA is used to improve the brightness of the paper pulp bleached by H2O2 or sodium dithionite. Furthermore, EDTA can be used as a stabilizer and for metal ion control. 

References:
Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.
</comment>
